This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on sentiment analysis of code-mixed social media text, which involves dealing with multiple languages in a single text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves machine learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves data processing and analysis, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
